               <p>JOHN SHAW. I live in <placeName id="t18251208-130-crimeloc663">High-street, St. Giles</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18251208-130-crimeloc663" type="placeName" value="High-street, St. Giles"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18251208-130-crimeloc663" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251208-130-off661 t18251208-130-crimeloc663"></join>, and <rs id="t18251208-130-viclabel664" type="occupation">deal in birds</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251208-130-victim713 t18251208-130-viclabel664"></join>. I had a live tame pigeon in a basket at my window, on the evening of the 23d of November, about seven o'clock; I went up stairs, and was called down - the two officers had brought the prisoner and the pigeon into my shop. The prisoner said he would satisfy me for it if I would not do any thing to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251208-130-person714">
                  ANGELIOUS 
                  BERTRAUN
               <interp inst="t18251208-130-person714" type="surname" value="BERTRAUN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-130-person714" type="given" value="ANGELIOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-130-person714" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Roberts in High-street, St. Giles's. I saw the prisoner and another young man pass Shaw's shop several times; the prisoner stood against the door; I crossed over, and saw the prisoner open the top of a basket, and take out something white. - I took him, and he threw the pigeon into the road.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251208-130-person715">
                  THOMAS 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18251208-130-person715" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
